    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ESM PDN connectivity procedure parameter handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `esm_proc_pdn_connectivity` function in `PdnConnectivity.c` had several issues causing unexpected behavior when establishing PDN connections. This fix resolves parameter name mismatches and variable shadowing that were causing incorrect procedure transaction identity handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/ESM/PdnConnectivity.c`: Fixed parameter name mismatch between header and implementation\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/ESM/PdnConnectivity.c`: Removed extra spaces in member access operators  \n- `openair3/NAS/UE/ESM/PdnConnectivity.c`: Resolved variable name conflict that was shadowing the pti parameter\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/ESM/PdnConnectivity.c`: Updated documentation to match parameter names\n\n### Reproduction\nUsers may experience issues when attempting to establish PDN connections where:\n- Procedure transaction identities are not properly assigned\n- PDN connection establishment fails unexpectedly\n- Memory management issues occur due to improper PTI handling\n\nThe issue manifests when calling `esm_proc_pdn_connectivity()` with `to_define=true` and a valid `pti` pointer, where the function would incorrectly handle the procedure transaction identity assignment due to the variable shadowing bug.\n"
}